28#ifndef REGRESS_TESTUTILS_H_INCLUDED_
29#define REGRESS_TESTUTILS_H_INCLUDED_
30
31#include "event2/dns.h"
32
33struct regress_dns_server_table {
34 const char *q;
35 const char *anstype;
36 const char *ans;
37 int seen;
38 int lower;
39};
40
41struct evdns_server_port *
42regress_get_dnsserver(struct event_base *base,
43 ev_uint16_t *portnum,
44 evutil_socket_t *psock,
45 evdns_request_callback_fn_type cb,
46 void *arg);
47
48/* Helper: return the port that a socket is bound on, in host order. */
49int regress_get_socket_port(evutil_socket_t fd);
50
51/* used to look up pre-canned responses in a search table */
52void regress_dns_server_cb(
53 struct evdns_server_request *req, void *data);
54
55/* globally allocates a dns server that serves from a search table */
56int regress_dnsserver(struct event_base *base, ev_uint16_t *port,
57 struct regress_dns_server_table *seach_table);
58
59/* clean up the global dns server resources */
60void regress_clean_dnsserver(void);
61
62struct evconnlistener;
63struct sockaddr;
64int regress_get_listener_addr(struct evconnlistener *lev,
65 struct sockaddr *sa, ev_socklen_t *socklen);
66
67#endif /* REGRESS_TESTUTILS_H_INCLUDED_ */
